               [clinicaltrials.gov identifier NCT00393692],
               Directional-Spread-in-Geographic-Atrophy [NCT02051998]) were
               included in the analysis. Serial fundus autofluorescence images
               were annotated using semiautomated image analysis software to
               determine the lesion area, circularity, perimeter, and caliper
               diameters. These variables and the fundus autofluorescence
               phenotype were evaluated for prediction of the future square
               root progression rates using linear mixed-effects models.
               RESULTS: For the combined model, leave-one-out cross validation
